*global keyword in a fuction introduces a pointer to the global variable.Then the same variable cant be ceated locally.
Having global variables in a program is not good thing.It creates many dependencies
Functions are first class entities-can be treated like an object
*A function can be embedded in a list
*when a function is defined,in the address stored in the function name, is the bytecode of the function body.

*function can be passed as a parameter to a function-Higher order functions

